cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.CR, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the study of routing overhead in wireless multihop networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the impact of network parameters on routing performance, which involves the analysis of information flow and transmission in the network. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents a study of three reactive routing protocols and their route discovery and maintenance mechanisms, which involves the analysis of data structures and algorithms used in these protocols. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may touch upon the security aspects of routing protocols in wireless networks, as route monitoring overhead is added to the generalized network models. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper may involve the study of control systems and optimization techniques to improve the routing performance in wireless networks.
